# Official D&D 5E Class Reference

Short reference for official classes in this project’s structure: feature progression, resource model, and key levels. Use when designing custom classes to stay 5E-consistent and avoid clashing with core norms. Format follows **custom-dnd-classes** (`.cursor/rules/custom-dnd-classes.mdc`).

---

## Druid

### Class Overview
**Role:** Full caster (controller/support), primal magic and Wild Shape  
**Primary Ability Score(s):** Wisdom  
**Power Fantasy:** Drawing on the divine essence of nature to cast spells and assume beast forms; versatile prepared caster with strong out-of-combat and control options.  
**Design Notes:** Long-rest spell slots (full caster progression); Wild Shape uses recharge on short or long rest. Subclass at 2nd level; power curve is spell level, not Extra Attack.

---

